*Problem statement : inconsistent execution of syllabus followed by various colleges and Lack of personalized tutoring offered in student domain.*                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Context: Many students in private colleges, such as RV, MSRIT, and BMS, often struggle with navigating their unique curricula and academic challenges. While colleges generally follow the VTU (Visvesvaraya Technological University) pattern, the execution and interpretation of the syllabus can vary significantly between institutions. This inconsistency may leave students feeling unsupported and unprepared for their assessments.

Proposed Solution: Peer Tutoring Platform
Overview: Develop a website that connects students with senior tutors from the same college, facilitating an accessible and relevant tutoring experience. This platform will leverage the knowledge of senior students who have successfully navigated the same syllabus and can provide tailored support.

Key Features:
Local Tutor Matching:

Students can find tutors within their college who understand the specific curriculum, allowing for more accurate and relevant guidance.
Offline Tutoring Sessions:

Promotes face-to-face interaction, enhancing learning engagement and allowing for a more personalized tutoring experience.
Syllabus Familiarity:

Tutors will be well-versed in their collegeâ€™s teaching methods and syllabus structure, minimizing confusion and focusing on relevant topics.
Flexible Scheduling:

The platform can include a scheduling feature that allows students to book sessions at their convenience, accommodating busy student schedules.
Feedback and Rating System:

Students can provide feedback on their tutoring experience, ensuring quality control and encouraging tutor accountability.
Resource Sharing:

Tutors can share useful resources, notes, and past exam papers, creating a collaborative learning environment.
Benefits:
Convenience: Students can easily connect with peers for academic support without the barriers often present with conventional tutoring services.

Peer Learning: Learning from someone who recently completed the same coursework can create a comfortable and relatable tutoring atmosphere.

Improved Academic Outcomes: Enhanced understanding of the syllabus and personalized learning can lead to better performance in exams.

Conclusion:
This initiative aims to create a supportive academic community within private colleges, fostering connections between students while addressing specific learning needs related to their unique syllabi. The peer tutoring platform not only addresses the immediate academic challenges but also contributes to a collaborative campus culture.